<section>elif (Else If)</section>

Sometimes there are multiple flight conditions to check â€” for example, maybe youâ€™ll hover instead of landing.

Thatâ€™s where elif comes in:

```python
wind_speed = 15

if wind_speed < 10:
    print("Takeoff approved!")
elif wind_speed < 20:
    print("Windy â€” hover mode only.")
else:
    print("Too windy â€” grounded.")
```

<section>Logical Operators</section>

You can combine multiple conditions using:

and â€” all must be True

or â€” at least one must be True

not â€” reverses the condition

Example:

```python
battery = 85
wind = 8
weather = "clear"

if battery > 50 and wind < 10 and weather == "clear":
    print("Takeoff approved âœ…")
else:
    print("Conditions unsafe âŒ")
```

